Distribution ( Fig. 38 , 40 ). Austria : near Graz (present study); near Mogersdorf (present study). Hungary : Abaliget Cave, Mecsek Mts. ( Verhoeff 1928 ); Kőszeg Mts. (see Korsós 1997: 89 ); Kovácsi Hill, Keszthelyi ( Loksa 1961 ); near Bélavár, Somogy ( Korsós 1998 ); near Szentgotthárd (present study). Romania : numerous caves in Banat and Oltenia (for details see Tabacaru 1965: 234–235 or
Tabacaru et al. 2003: 133
). Serbia : near Vrdnik, Fruška gora Mt. (present study). Slovenia : forest near Šalovci , Goričko (present study).
